  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REDUCTION/STABILISATION OF HIV INCIDENCE INCREASE CAPACITY TO PREVENT HIV (Human Immunodeficiency Virus)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ireland is working with UN agencies (under the leadership of UNAIDS) and will work with 4 local NGOs, to scale up coverage, utilization and access to quality SRH, HIV prevention, treatment, care and support services; while addressing socio-cultural and economic barriers hindering HIV preventive behaviours and constraint access to services. In addition, national and Karamoja region&apos;s capacity for planning, coodination, sustainable financing and information systems for tracking programmes will be strengthened.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this budget line is to reduce the number of new HIV infections among youth and adults, in particular amongst adolescent girls</narrative>
  </description>
